OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778904285
OL,3,CDon't swim in these 'bathing waters',
OL,4,Cwarn experts
OL,6,FIt's because designation includes
OL,7,Ffactors such as popularity and
OL,8,Flavatory facilities - even in some
OL,9,Flocations where water quality is
OL,10,Fofficially rated "poor".
OL,12,FToday, 13 new locations were
OL,13,Fofficially listed as bathing sites. It
OL,14,Fbrings the total to 464 across
OL,15,FEngland, spanning beach and river
OL,16,Flocations. But 32 areas officially
OL,17,Fclassified as bathing waters are not
OL,18,Fcurrently suitable for bathing. The
OL,19,Ffull water quality data and bathing
OL,20,Fwater designations can be viewed here.
OL,26,@rD@ROUrD@WO]
